  "prompt": "How can evaporated milk be substituted for condensed milk?",
  "response": "Evaporated milk and condensed milk are quite different, so they cannot be directly substituted for each other without modifications:\n\n1. Sugar content:\n- Condensed milk is very sweet and thick\n- Evaporated milk is unsweetened and thinner\n\n2. Substitution method:\n- If using evaporated milk in place of condensed milk, you'll need to:\n   a) Add sugar (about 1 cup sugar per 12 oz can of evaporated milk)\n   b) Simmer the mixture to reduce and thicken it\n\n3. Alternative approach:\n- Mix evaporated milk with sugar and heat until it becomes thick and syrupy\n- Cool before using in recipes\n\n4. Best uses:\n- This substitution works best in baked goods and desserts\n- May not work as well in no-bake recipes that rely on condensed milk's thick consistency\n\n5. Ratio:\n- Generally use equal amounts of modified evaporated milk to replace condensed milk\n\nKeep in mind that the texture and sweetness might be slightly different from the original recipe.",
